<subSubSection id="46E76549FFEB543BAAE4FB01B9C0FC75" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" type="description">
<paragraph id="0E4236C2FFEB543BAAE4FB01BE1DFDC9" blockId="4.[151,1437,440,1188]" box="[199,1320,548,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="3C89EAD0FFEB543BAAE4FB01BA6CFDC9" bold="true" box="[199,345,548,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Description.</emphasis>
Description is based only on female specimens, since males are absent in our material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E4236C2FFEB543BAAE4FB6CBEB1FD5D" blockId="4.[151,1437,440,1188]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
Fairly shiny, entirely yellowish green, forewing with few brown speckles in middle of costal margin. Face occasionally somewhat darker in upper part, spots on sides of frons sometimes brownish, almost invisible. Midline of pro- and mesonotum and triangular spots in lateral angles of mesonotum whitish (
<figureCitation id="96C62A47FFEB543BA9C2FBB4BF52FD5D" box="[993,1127,656,683]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Figs. 13–15</figureCitation>
). Proepimeron unmarked.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E4236C2FFEB543BAAE4FB90BA00FCE1" blockId="4.[151,1437,440,1188]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
Apex of crown and anterior margin of pronotum sharply angular; crown in dorsal view of almost the same length in middle and next to eyes (
<figureCitation id="96C62A47FFEB543BA809FBFCB94AFD05" box="[554,639,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Median keel on face, pro-, and mesonotum well developed, whitish (
<figureCitation id="96C62A47FFEB543BAABCFBD8BA1CFCE1" box="[159,297,764,791]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Figs. 14–15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E4236C2FFEB543BAAE4FA04BE54FC96" blockId="4.[151,1437,440,1188]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
2 
<superScript id="F9889B8AFFEB543BAAF6FA05BBD0FCD8" attach="left" box="[213,229,800,814]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor very narrow, with 5–8 unusually small, sometimes indistinct preapical teeth (
<figureCitation id="96C62A47FFEB543BAF47FA04BBD7FCA9" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Figs. 59–60</figureCitation>
). Female 7 
<superScript id="F9889B8AFFEB543BAB7FFA61BA5CFCA4" attach="left" box="[348,361,836,850]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">th</superScript>
sternite of usual shape, triangular, with small shallow notch on hind margin (
<figureCitation id="96C62A47FFEB543BAEE8FA60BE61FC96" box="[1227,1364,837,864]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Figs. 61–62</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E4236C2FFEB543BAAE4FA4CB9C0FC75" blockId="4.[151,1437,440,1188]" box="[199,757,873,900]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
Body length (including tegmina): 
<specimenCount id="18FBFD4BFFEB543BA867FA4CB96CFC75" box="[580,601,873,899]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
